[[Image:Derbent winter.jpg|thumb|300px|The Sassanian fortress of [[Derbent]], whose [[Third Perso-Turkic War|Siege and Sack]] during the Khazar Invasions was described in detail by the author of ''History''.]]
'''Movses Kaghankatvatsi''' ({{lang-hy|<U+0544><U+0578><U+057E><U+057D><U+0565><U+057D> <U+053F><U+0561><U+0572><U+0561><U+0576><U+056F><U+0561><U+057F><U+057E><U+0561><U+0581><U+056B>}} ''Mows<U+025B>s Ka<U+026C>ankatwac<U+2018><U+025B>''), also referred to as '''Movses Daskhurantsi''' ({{lang-hy|<U+0544><U+0578><U+057E><U+057D><U+0565><U+057D> <U+0534><U+0561><U+057D><U+056D><U+0578><U+0582><U+0580><U+0561><U+0576><U+0581><U+056B>}} ''Mows<U+025B>s Dasxu<U+027E>anc<U+2018><U+025B>''), was a medieval [[Armenian people|Armenian]] [[historian]]  believed to have authored [[The History of the Country of Albania]].<ref>{{tr icon}} {{cite book| last = <U+0130>stanbul <U+00DC>niversitesi <U+0130>sl<U+00E2>m Tetkikleri Enstit<U+00FC>s<U+00FC>| first =| author link = | title = <U+0130>sl<U+00E2>m Tetkikleri Enstit<U+00FC>s<U+00FC> dergisi| publisher = Edebiyat Fak<U+00FC>ltesi Matbaas<U+0131>| year =1953| location = <U+0130>stanbul| isbn =| page = 35 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book| last = Vasiliev| first = A.A.| title = The Second Russian Attack on Constantinople| publisher = [[Dumbarton Oaks Papers]] Vol. 6| year = 1951| isbn =| author = link =| page = 181 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book| last = Cameron| first = Averil| title =Agathias of the Sassanians| publisher = Dumbarton Oaks Papers Vol. 23| year = 1969| location =| isbn =| page = 153 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Oshanin| first = Lev Vasilievich | title =Anthropological Composition of the Population of Central Asia, and the Ethnogenesis of Its Peoples | publisher = Peabody Museum | year =1964 | location =  | isbn = | author = link =| page = 24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book
